1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 d5 4. Bg2 Be7 5. Nf3 O-O 6. O-O dxc4 7. Ne5
{ This is White's other main line, second in popularity to 7 Qc2. Arguably, however, this is the most ambitious move in the position. We will be introduced to other alternatives on moves 7 and 6 in Chapter Four. }
7... Nc6
{ This is generally accepted as Black's most theoretically reliable answer. Yes, it looks weird; more details will be provided in the third chapter. }
