1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 e6 3. g3 d5 4. Bg2 Be7 5. Nf3 O-O 6. O-O dxc4 7. Qc2 b6 8. Ne5
Qxd4 9. Nxf7
{ This move has only been played once, but it's one of the top choices of the computer, so I figured it was worth a brief mention. White is trying to grab one more pawn before taking the Rook. }
9... Nd5
{ You snooze, you lose. Naturally, we don't actually have to give White the Rook now. }
10. Ng5 Bxg5 11. Bxg5 Bb7
{ Black's pawn structure is slightly questionable, yes, and White does have the Bishop pair, but an extra pawn is an extra pawn. The first player has compensation, but I don't think it's enough to give him an advantage. }
