Qxd4 9. Bxa8 Qxe5 10. Nd2
{ This doesn't seem like a great move, either. Again, this is because the e2 pawn is dropping. }
10... Qxe2 11. Bf3 Qd3 12. Qxc4 Ba6 13. Qxd3 Bxd3
{ This isn't a position to be worried about with Black - we have two pawns for the exchange, and a nice and mobile Queenside majority, which advances very quickly. Check out the game Goganov-Bukavshin, Khanty-Mansiysk 2015 for an illustration of how Black can win these positions. }
