Qxd4 9. Bxa8 Qxe5 10. Bf3 Nd5 11. Qxc4 Ba6 12. Qa4 c5 13. Nd2 Rc8
{ 13...Bxe2?? 14 Re1 is worth avoiding. } 14. Rd1 c4
{ I'd like to push ...c4 before ...b5 in order to rule out Qa4-e4  (despite the ending probably not being so bad for Black)  . }
15. Nf1 Bc5
{ In the game Nyback-Pihlajasalo, Helsinki 2015, Black played 15...b5?!, when the computer gives 16 Qa5! - the point being after 16...Bd8 17 Qd2,   16...Bb4  17  Rxd5!  the Knight on d5 is hit three times, and also pinned to mate on the back rank. I'm not sure how relevant this is practically speaking, considering the 2600 GM playing White missed it, but regardless, 15...Bc5 and only later ...b5  (Qa5, ...Bb6 - there's no back rank mate problems after Qd2)  . }
