{ Magnus Carlsen has actually had this position from the Black side - against Topalov in a 2007 blindfold game in Bilbao. He arrived here by transposition from a weird Queen's Indian line and chose 11...cxd4, which is fine, but, as I mentined earlier, Qxd4 and Ne5 can be slightly annoying. Therefore, I'd like to stick to the usual ...Nbd7 then ...c5 then ...Rc8 formula. }
11... Rc8 12. Rac1 a6 { Standard. } 13. dxc5 b5 14. Qd3 Nxc5
{ Black had equalized in Slawinski-Ryska, correspondence 2010. } *

