{ This is another typical scenario in which Black has solved his  (only?)  problem - the backward c-pawn, and now just needs to activate the rest of his pieces to achieve a fine position. }
11. Nc3 Qe7 12. a3 Rc8
{ Good move - annoying the White Queen ASAP is often a good idea, while in this case, the Knight is still deciding whether it prefers c6 or d7. }
13. Qa4 Nbd7 14. Rac1 a6
{ Beginning the standard Queenside expansion plan. Black was at least equal in Izzat-Brown, PRO League 2018. }
