{ This would probably work out better for White if his Knight were on d2 - out of the tempo-range of the pawn, and ready to hop into c4. }
13. a5 Qa6 14. Na4
{ This is White's point, trying to hold back ...c5. However... } 14... c5
{ ...it turns out it's possible anyway! } 15. dxc5 Be4
{ After White's Queen moves, we can take back on c5 with a healthy position, as in Christiansen-Urkedal, Oslo 2015. }
