b5 9. Qc2 Bb7 10. Nc3 Nbd7 11. Rd1 Qb6 12. e4 c5 13. d5 exd5
{ This is a logical move, but it contains one drawback... } 14. e5
{ Excellent move - now 14...Ne8 15 Nxd5 would be kind of depressing, so Black is half-committed to sacrificing a piece. }
14... d4 15. exf6 Nxf6
{ 15...dxc3 16 fxe7 wouldn't go so well for Black. Black has two pawns, a mobile centre, and activity for his piece. This position was briefly discussed during the chess24 Candidates broadcast, where Peter Svidler explained that he felt White should be able to consolidate. To be honest, I trust his judgement over the computer's ever-shifting evaluation. Nevertheless, for a practical game, this still looks like an interesting try. }
