{ This is Gustafsson's recommendation. The natural Rad8 is actually less to the point, as after 16 Qe3 or 16 Qf4, White is merely pushed to make a move he was going to play anyway. Instead, Black zeroes in on the soft spot on e2. Bh3 is also an acceptable move, by the way. }
