bxa3 Bd7 9. Qc2
{ Attempting to simply win the pawn back. We don't really have a good way to defend it, but fortunately, keeping our extra pawn was never really our priority. }
9... Bc6 10. Qxc4 Nbd7 11. Bf4 Rc8
{ Good move - defending the c-pawn in preparation for ...Bd5 and ...c5. } 12.
Rac1 Bd5 13. Qc2 c5
{ Black had equalized in the game Przedmojski-Zeberski, Poraj 2003. Compared to the usual lines where we get ...c5 in, White has the Bishop pair, but Black has an intact pawn structure. These two factors more or less balance each other out. }
