{ The theory goes on, but I think this is a reasonable place to stop. White has two Bishops and a Queenside majority, but Black has an imposing centre. Play is roughly balanced. Black should look to develop his pieces, while after a typical exchanging maneuver Nd2-e4, he can look into ...Nxe4, ...Kh8 and ...f5. }
